This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on facial expression recognition using machine learning techniques. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The study also explores the balance between speed and accuracy, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses a social need related to Autism Spectrum Disorder, which could place it in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of computer vision and machine learning techniques for facial expression recognition could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
